Data Story on song lyrics

Music is a great tool to tell story and express feelings we cant grasp. And music in different genres tend to convey emotion in different ways. Although the genres classifications may be subjective and even overlap, there are still some shared characteristics represented in lyrics through genre breakdown.

Word Analysis

Does patterns varies in song lyrics between genres and time? I try to compare the most frequently used words in different genres to get an answer. I take the 6 most popular genreCountry, Hiphop, Jazz, Mental, Pop, and Rock music as examples, and roughly divide the time into 2 stages of before/after 2010.

From the plots and cloud above, the word like love, baby, girl,youre are always used in lyrics all the time, words like cowboy,bubba,artifacts which used to frequently appear, is rarely shown any more. And words like camouflage,troll,afterparty,pirate starts to shown in lyrics in recent years.

## [1] 122376

I also list the top 8 frequently used word in every genres, which shows the similar results. among all the 122,376 lines of lyrics, 51182 of which have love included. The word love show the core emotion from old times to today in every genres, except the mental music which is presented below. Mental music tend to focus on the singers inner world rather than the external emotional connections. However, love in different genres of music can be different from each others. I compare the word often used in the subset of data which includes love,heart,baby,youre From the results above, I can see jazz and hiphop music have clear difference in word choose. To express love, Jazz musicians prefer more elegant vocabulary like dream,blue,night, while rappers prefers more colloquial and unrefined words.

Sentiment Analysis

I would also like to examine which genre is the most positive or negative overall?

From the plot above, we can see the lyrics in Jazz music deliver the most positive values, and Hip-Hop music contains the most negative messages. These are corresponding to our findings in the word choice to express love.

I take 6 different music genres, which are strongly affected by emotion, as examples, and look deeper to analyze which words contributed most to the positive and negative sentiment values. it turns out to be , jazz, R&B, and Pop music on the left contains frequent usage of love,happy,true,care, which are quite reasonable to be positive drivers. however, Hip-Hop, Mental, and Rock music mentions a lot aboutill,shit,die,hell as the the strongest contributors to be negative lyrics.

Moreover, artists, as brilliant storytellers, also have fixed lyrics style, therefore, I list top 10 artists with the most negative songs.

Conclusions

  1. Song lyrics changes with time, but love is the core emotion from past to present

  2. Different genres of music have different patterns and word choice to express feelings.

  3. Jazz music delivers the most positive messages and Hip-hop music delivers the most negative.
